The paper discusses advances in neural network based classifiers and their use in representation learning, specifically comparing supervised learning with generative models such as GANs. This topic is most closely related to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG), which is the most likely category. Computer Vision (cs.CV) is also relevant as the paper discusses the ImageNet challenge. Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is another possible category as the paper discusses the potential for stronger AI. Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) is relevant as the paper discusses neural networks. Finally, Computation and Language (cs.CL) is a possible category as the paper discusses the utility of good representations for transfer learning, which is relevant to natural language processing.
